text: From Barrons this morning (Randy Forsyth Up and Down Wall Street) "That reminds Doug Kass of Seabreeze Partners of the once-hot funds, such as the former Janus Twenty. “In every stock market cycle there is a dominant investor who captures the market’s zeitgeist by incorporating

and reflecting the ideas and beliefs of the times,” he writes in his blog. And that there is no price too high to pay for those concepts, in this case disruptive technologies, most notably Tesla (TSLA), ARKK’s largest holding." Thanks for the shout out, Randy! @jimcramer
